<div class="col-lg-12">
  <center><h4>What is Democratize!?</h4></center>
          <p>Democratize! is a web/mobile app that serves as a town hall for cities. In this "virtual town hall", users share any useful information that is currently affecting their community.
             This can be through an opinion, a piece of relevant news, or even an attempt at creating a grassroots movement. What sets Democratize! apart from other networks is that it is centered on the community at large rather than
            individual. Everything on Democratize! is subect to the democratic process. Democratize! seeks to bridge the gap between the community and their political  representation by connecting them in a new and exciting way.
          </p>

  <center><h4>How do I use Democratize!?</h4></center>
          <p>You can view any post in any city/community but to actaully make your voice heard, you have to sign up(which is relatively painless). Once registered you can post and comment on anything.
            Utilizing <%= link_to "reddit", "http://www.reddit.com", target: "_blank" %> voting and commenting features but with a local-centric focus similar to <%= link_to "craigslist", "http://www.craigslist.com", target: "_blank" %>, Democratize! truly is a "virtual town hall".
          </p>
  <p>
          Democratize! Tulsa encourages all political parties to present their opinion in a respectful manner, but disagreements are encouraged! Don't be afraid to enlist your friends to sign up and vote on your posts to ensure that your opinion
          is the first one seen. The focus of Democratize! Tulsa is to connect you and your respective city councilors in a way never before tried. 
        </p>
        
  <center><h4><%= link_to "Democratize! Tulsa", "/cities/1-tulsa" %></h4></center>
        <p>Democratize! Tulsa is a hub for users to share news with their neighbors about local politics, activities, events, concerns, etc. Tulsa is the second largest city in Oklahoma and has a long and
          rich heritage of politics. In fact, <a href="http://www.forbes.com/2009/04/01/cities-city-ten-lifestyle-real-estate-livable-cities.html">Forbes</a> even voted it one of America's most liveable cities. Tulsa, OK
          is a town that does not necessarily vote along party lines in mayor elections so having a debate platform is critical so ensure that Tulsa citizens can make informed decisions. Democratize! Tulsa is the best resource for 
          political debate and unbiased news.
          </p>
  <center><h4><%= link_to "Democratize! Oklahoma City", "/cities/2-oklahomacity" %></h4></center>
        <p> Democratize! Oklahoma City is the second city to be supported by Democratize!. Oklahoma City is the largest city in Oklahoma City and it only continues to grow bigger. Democratize! Oklahoma City will serve as hub to serve the political needs of this ever booming city.
        </p>     
          
